Name: allowplaintext
Type: SWITCH
Default-Value: 0
Last-Modified: 3.0.0

If enabled, allows the use of cleartext passwords on the wire.

By default, the use of cleartext passwords requires a TLS/SSL encryption
layer to be negotiated prior to any cleartext authentication mechanisms
being advertised or allowed.  To require a TLS/SSL encryption layer to be
negotiated prior to ANY authentication, see the :imapdconf:`tls_required`
option.
